{
  "profile_id": "client-edge-dont-have-time-001",
  "coach_config_id": "naive-aoa",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I'm not in a position to slow down right now. I've got a Series A pitch in six weeks and a team that's watching every move I make — so if this is useful, great, but I need it to be efficient."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What would it cost you if this wasn't efficient?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Time. Which right now is the only currency that matters. Every hour I'm not moving the ball forward is an hour I'm not closing investors or fixing the product gaps they're going to ask about. So — what have you got?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I'm curious about something. You came here — to a coaching conversation — six weeks out from the most important pitch of your company's life. What made you do that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "My co-founder basically insisted. She thinks I'm — look, she flagged some things about how I'm showing up with the team. People are apparently reading stress off me and it's affecting morale. So fine, I'm here. I'm open to concrete feedback on how to manage that. What do I do differently in the next six weeks?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What did she say specifically — about how you're showing up?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "She said I'm making people feel like they can't bring me problems. Like everything's on fire and there's no room for anything that isn't a direct line to the pitch. Which — I mean, she's not wrong that the pitch has to be the priority, but apparently people are starting to self-censor and that's creating blind spots. So yeah, I get it, I need to be more — I don't know, accessible or whatever. What's the playbook for that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You said \"she's not wrong\" pretty quickly there. What's it like to hear that people are self-censoring around you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "It's — not great. Obviously. I don't want that. But I also understand why it's happening, it's a high-pressure period and everyone's feeling it. It's not like I'm doing it on purpose. So the question is just what's the fastest way to correct for it before it becomes a real problem. Is there a communication framework or something? I've seen stuff about psychological safety, there's probably a quick version of that I can implement."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I notice you moved pretty fast from \"not great\" to explaining it and fixing it. What's underneath \"not great\"?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I don't know what you mean. \"Not great\" means it's a problem I need to solve. That's — that's just how I process things. Identify the issue, find the fix, move on. That's what's gotten us this far.\n\nWhat are you actually asking me?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I'm asking what you feel when you find out that the people you're leading are afraid to come to you."
    }
  ],
